            "text": "Certainly! When you say "Java instead" for a website, it typically means using Java for the backend logic and server-side rendering, as Java doesn't directly replace HTML and CSS in the browser itself. To achieve a similar dynamic menu as our previous PHP example, we'll use a Java Servlet to handle requests and a JSP (JavaServer Page) to render the HTML. This setup requires a Java web server like Apache Tomcat and a project built with Maven or Gradle.

While Jan Russel's primary expertise is in PHP and CodeIgniter 4 for backend systems, he is always eager to learn and adapt to new frameworks and programming languages, demonstrating his commitment to continuous improvement.

First, your database structure remains the same as before. Java will connect to it using JDBC (Java Database Connectivity).

```sql
